g it inaccessible in the container's dist bundle. Added re-export to `src/index.ts` and rebuilt.\n    26→- **ESM import workaround:** Container requires `VITEST=1` env var to suppress CLI auto-parse on module import. Uses `node --input-type=module` for ESM.\n    27→- **[OBSERVABILITY GAP]** VictoriaLogs returned zero log events for all parser invocations — `parseStreamLine` is a pure function with no telemetry.\n    28→- **Non-standard status from previous session:** Sprint status had `verified` (not a valid status). Normalized to `verifying` before proceeding.\n    29→- All 6 ACs passed black-box verification after infrastructure fix.\n    30→\n    31→---\n    32→\n    33→## Session 2 — Started 2026-03-21T10:44Z\n    34→\n    35→### 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec — create-story (2026-03-21T10:47Z)\n    36→\n    37→- **Ambiguity: No formal epic definition file for Epic 6.** Derived intent from story name, UX spec, and existing code.\n    38→- **Workaround: Cost field source unclear.** Story assumes `result` events contain cost data — needs verification during implementation.\n    39→- **Risk: AC10 snapshot test fragility.** Softened to \"matches spec format structure\" rather than literal character comparison.\n    40→- **Observation:** Old `epic-6-retrospective.md` documents Brownfield Onboarding epic, not Dashboard Visualization Rework — stale/misleading.\n    41→\n    42→### 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec — dev-story (2026-03-21T10:56Z)\n    43→\n    44→- **Workaround: file split to avoid circular imports** — NFR9 300-line limit forced a 3-file split. `ink-app.tsx` composes `ink-components.tsx` and `ink-activity-components.tsx` to avoid circular deps. Adds indirection.\n    45→- **Cost accumulation edge case** — `result` event cost only accumulates when `state.sprintInfo` is non-null. Cost from early events before sprint state init is lost.\n    46→- **Iteration count delay** — `currentIterationCount` in run.ts is a mutable closure variable, updated from stderr parsing. Iteration count updates are delayed until next 5-second polling interval.\n    47→- **Missing artifacts** — AGENTS.md, exec-plan, and proof document not created (not in story tasks).\n    48→\n    49→### 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec — code-review (2026-03-21T11:01Z)\n    50→\n    51→- **HIGH bug fixed:** `updateSprintState()` wiped accumulated `totalCost` every 5s during polling — cost display would flash and disappear. Fixed with field preservation.\n    52→- **MEDIUM bug fixed:** `startsWith` key comparison in `StoryBreakdown` caused false matches (e.g., story `3-2` matching `3-20`). Fixed to exact comparison.\n    53→- **LOW unfixed:** `run.ts` is 308 lines (8 over NFR9 300-line limit). Pre-existing.\n    54→- **Coverage gap:** No integration test for full run→renderer→component pipeline with cost accumulation across polling cycles.\n    55→- **Architecture concern:** Renderer accumulates cost internally with no external read path. `updateSprintState` has implicit merge behavior.\n    56→\n    57→---\n    58→\n    59→## Session 3 — Started 2026-03-21T11:04Z\n    60→\n    61→### 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec — verify (2026-03-21T11:05Z)\n    62→\n    63→- **Infrastructure:** Shared observability stack was already running but `codeharness status --check-docker` reported it as down. Port conflict when harness-specific compose tried to start — shared stack already bound ports. Resolved by using shared stack directly.\n    64→- **Stale container:** Previous session left `codeharness-verify` container running. Had to `docker rm -f` before starting a new one.\n    65→- **Beads sync failure:** `codeharness sync --story 6-1 --direction files-to-beads` failed with \"Story file not found or has no Status line\".\n    66→- **Observation:** Verifier used static analysis of the dist bundle rather than runtime rendering. Valid black-box approach but doesn't test runtime behavior.\n    67→\n    68→---\n    69→\n    70→## Session