{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Gd9NkGEpeiok5Jp2wExpFY","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Story created at `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/7-2-fix-bats-runtime-tests.md`.\n\nSummary of what was done:\n- Read sprint-status.yaml, confirmed `7-2-fix-bats-runtime-tests` is the next backlog story\n- Read the existing thin story file (had wrong title \"Story 6-2\", minimal 3 ACs, no tasks)\n- Investigated the actual codebase: runtime-validator.ts, audit dimensions, deps.ts, onboard.bats, test_helper.bash, CI workflows, package.json\n- Confirmed BATS is not installed locally (`command not found`)\n- Rewrote the story with 7 ACs, 6 task groups, dev notes, architecture compliance, and references\n\nAC verification tags assigned:\n- **cli-verifiable**: ACs 1, 3, 4, 5, 6 (registry inspection, npm test, test file review, deps tests, audit output)\n- **integration-required**: ACs 2, 7 (fresh env install, CI pipeline behavior)\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Problems encountered:**\n- The existing story file had the wrong title (\"Story 6-2\" instead of \"Story 7.2\") and was extremely thin (3 ACs, no tasks, no references). Overwrote entirely.\n\n**Workarounds applied:**\n- None.\n\n**Risks identified:**\n- AC #4 (fixing 14 skipped onboard.bats tests) is the largest task and has design ambiguity: the tests were broken because `onboard.sh` now delegates to the TS CLI which needs full init. Rewriting them to test the delegation layer (arg parsing, error exits) is feasible but the dev needs to decide the right granularity. Removing them entirely is simpler but loses integration coverage.\n- AC #1 uses `brew install bats-core` as primary — this only works on macOS. The `npm install -g bats` fallback should cover Linux, but `npm install -g bats` installs a different package (`bats` npm package) that may not be 100% compatible with `bats-core`. Dev should verify the npm fallback produces a working `bats` binary.\n- AC #7 (CI impact) is tagged integration-required because we cannot verify CI pipeline changes locally.\n\n**Observations:**\n- The `npm test` script runs `bats tests/` — this means BATS is a hard requirement for `npm test` to work at all, yet it's marked `critical: false` in the registry. This is intentional (audit degrades gracefully) but means `npm test` will still fail if BATS isn't installed. The runtime validator already handles this gracefully by catching the error.\n- Epic 7 in the epics-overhaul.md is titled \"OpenSearch Backend\" — but the sprint-status.yaml's Epic 7 is \"Onboarding — Compliance Gaps\". These are different epics with the same number from different planning cycles. The story follows the sprint-status.yaml version."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a94153f3123a25f89 (use SendMessage with to: 'a94153f3123a25f89' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 41061\ntool_uses: 24\nduration_ms: 134973</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"00ac9844-6f35-4a8e-aae2-09915fdc37cf","uuid":"ad7ea478-d645-462b-bb8b-620eb2f7a81c","timestamp":"2026-03-21T12:07:23.661Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /create-story for story 7-2-fix-bats-runtime-tests. The sprint-status.yaml is at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml. Auto-discover the next backlog story and create it. For each AC, append `<!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->` or `<!-- verification: integration-required -->` based on whether the AC can be verified by running CLI commands in a subprocess. ACs referencing workflows, sprint planning, user sessions, or external system interactions should be tagged as integration-required. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Problems encountered (errors, ambiguities in epic definition, missing context)\n- Workarounds applied (anything you did that felt hacky or suboptimal)\n- Risks identified (ACs that seem untestable, unclear requirements, missing dependencies)\n- Observations (anything surprising or noteworthy about this story)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`","agentId":"a94153f3123a25f89","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Story created at `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/7-2-fix-bats-runtime-tests.md`.\n\nSummary of what was done:\n- Read sprint-status.yaml, confirmed `7-2-fix-bats-runtime-tests` is the next backlog story\n- Read the existing thin story file (had wrong title \"Story 6-2\", minimal 3 ACs, no tasks)\n- Investigated the actual codebase: runtime-validator.ts, audit dimensions, deps.ts, onboard.bats, test_helper.bash, CI workflows, package.json\n- Confirmed BATS is not installed locally (`command not found`)\n- Rewrote the story with 7 ACs, 6 task groups, dev notes, architecture compliance, and references\n\nAC verification tags assigned:\n- **cli-verifiable**: ACs 1, 3, 4, 5, 6 (registry inspection, npm test, test file review, deps tests, audit output)\n- **integration-required**: ACs 2, 7 (fresh env install, CI pipeline behavior)\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Problems encountered:**\n- The existing story file had the wrong title (\"Story 6-2\" instead of \"Story 7.2\") and was extremely thin (3 ACs, no tasks, no references). Overwrote entirely.\n\n**Workarounds applied:**\n- None.\n\n**Risks identified:**\n- AC #4 (fixing 14 skipped onboard.bats tests) is the largest task and has design ambiguity: the tests were broken because `onboard.sh` now delegates to the TS CLI which needs full init. Rewriting them to test the delegation layer (arg parsing, error exits) is feasible but the dev needs to decide the right granularity. Removing them entirely is simpler but loses integration coverage.\n- AC #1 uses `brew install bats-core` as primary — this only works on macOS. The `npm install -g bats` fallback should cover Linux, but `npm install -g bats` installs a different package (`bats` npm package) that may not be 100% compatible with `bats-core`. Dev should verify the npm fallback produces a working `bats` binary.\n- AC #7 (CI impact) is tagged integration-required because we cannot verify CI pipeline changes locally.\n\n**Observations:**\n- The `npm test` script runs `bats tests/` — this means BATS is a hard requirement for `npm test` to work at all, yet it's marked `critical: false` in the registry. This is intentional (audit degrades gracefully) but means `npm test` will still fail if BATS isn't installed. The runtime validator already handles this gracefully by catching the error.\n- Epic 7 in the epics-overhaul.md is titled \"OpenSearch Backend\" — but the sprint-status.yaml's Epic 7 is \"Onboarding — Compliance Gaps\". These are different epics with the same number from different planning cycles. The story follows the sprint-status.yaml version."}],"totalDurationMs":134973,"totalTokens":41061,"totalToolUseCount":24,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3072,"cache_read_input_tokens":37263,"output_tokens":725,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3072},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
