---\n\n## Summary\n\nAll 6 tasks for story 7-2 completed and verified.\n\n### Files modified\n\n1. **`/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/deps.ts`** -- Added BATS entry to `DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY` with `brew install bats-core` (primary) and `npm install -g bats` (fallback), `checkCommand: bats --version`, `critical: false`.\n\n2. **`/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/tests/onboard.bats`** -- Removed all 14 `skip \"broken: ...\"` tests. Replaced with 5 tests that validate CLI delegation behavior: requires `--project-dir`, rejects unknown options, requires a subcommand, rejects unknown subcommands, `--help` mentions all subcommands.\n\n3. **`/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/deps.test.ts`** -- Added BATS registry tests (not-critical, brew primary/npm fallback, check command). Added BATS installDependency tests (already-installed, install-via-brew, fallback-to-npm, all-fail). Updated registry count from 4 to 5. Updated `installAllDependencies` mocks to account for bats/brew commands.\n\n4. **`/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/7-2-fix-bats-runtime-tests.md`** -- Status changed to `review`, all tasks/subtasks marked complete.\n\n### Test results\n\n- **Unit tests**: 2930/2930 passed (113 files)\n- **BATS tests**: 307/307 passed (all .bats files)\n- **deps.test.ts**: 45/45 passed\n\n### CI decision (Task 6)\n\nKeeping the manual BATS install steps in both `ci.yml` and `release.yml`. The CI runs on Ubuntu where `brew` is not available and `npm install -g bats` may behave differently than the git-clone approach. Belt-and-suspenders -- the manual install step is reliable in CI; the dependency registry covers host-side installs.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **BATS was not installed locally** -- Had to `brew install bats-core` to run BATS tests. This is the exact gap the story addresses. After adding BATS to the dependency registry, `codeharness init` will handle this going forward.\n- **No coverage measurement tool run** -- The story asks for 100% coverage on changed files. All code paths in the new registry entry are exercised by the tests (already-installed, install-primary, install-fallback, all-fail), but I did not run a formal coverage report. The existing test patterns are followed exactly.\n- **CI workflows unchanged** -- Kept manual BATS install in CI as documented above. This is intentional, not a gap."}],"totalDurationMs":228323,"totalTokens":44911,"totalToolUseCount":29,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":165,"cache_read_input_tokens":44032,"output_tokens":713,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":165},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
