{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PQwwHpWcc5MCgZNNZpZGVX","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Retrospective — 2026-03-21\n     2→\n     3→**Sprint:** Operational Excellence Sprint\n     4→**Session window:** ~04:21Z – ~04:45Z (approx 25 minutes)\n     5→**Sprint progress:** 15/20 stories done (75%), Epic 3 nearing completion\n     6→\n     7→---\n     8→\n     9→## 1. Session Summary\n    10→\n    11→| Story | Epic | Outcome | Phases Completed |\n    12→|-------|------|---------|-----------------|\n    13→| 3-3-onboard-alias | Epic 3: Audit Command | Verifying (all phases done, awaiting final verification) | create-story, dev-story, code-review |\n    14→\n    15→One story was attempted this session. It progressed through story creation, implementation, and code review without blocking failures. The story replaced a 478-line onboard command with a 40-line alias delegating to a shared audit handler — a 92% reduction in code.\n    16→\n    17→**Test results at session end:** 2783 tests passing across 119 files, 96.97% overall coverage, all files above 80% floor.\n    18→\n    19→---\n    20→\n    21→## 2. Issues Analysis\n    22→\n    23→### Bugs Discovered During Implementation\n    24→\n    25→- **Unsafe double type assertion** (HIGH) — `audit-action.ts:86` used `as unknown as Record<string, unknown>` to bypass TypeScript type safety. Fixed during code review by using spread operator instead.\n    26→- **Dead branch guard** (MEDIUM) — `audit-action.ts:101` had a `fixStories &&` check that was always true at that point. Simplified to `else`.\n    27→\n    28→### Workarounds Applied (Tech Debt Introduced)\n    29→\n    30→- **`console.log` in audit-action.ts:111** (LOW, not fixed) — The shared handler uses `console.log` directly instead of output utilities. Established codebase pattern but violates project conventions. Needs a new `raw()` output utility to fix properly. **Tracked as tech debt.**"}]},"parent_tool_us